{"at": "2026-06-26T09:15:49.489991+00:00", "event_id": "01KW1KDHVJ517SNNWFCWRKWA18", "event_type": "DecisionPointOpened", "payload": {"actor_id": "cli", "actor_type": "human", "decision_point_id": "01KW1KDHVGWZ0QERDMV1CRJ15S", "input_key": "windows_base_normalization", "mission_id": "01KW1JXXTH8YVMADWF0G80H765", "mission_slug": "spec-kitty-home-isolation-01KW1JXX", "mission_type": "software-dev", "options": ["Normalize all Windows surfaces onto platformdirs base", "Strictly preserve current per-surface Windows paths", "Other"], "origin_flow": "plan", "origin_surface": "planning_interview", "phase": "PLAN", "question": "On unset Windows, several surfaces (sync config, queue, clock, tracker DB) currently leak to ~/.spec-kitty instead of the platformdirs app-data base used by daemon/auth/tracker-creds. Should the fix normalize ALL Windows surfaces onto the single platformdirs base, or strictly preserve each surface's exact current Windows path and only add the SPEC_KITTY_HOME override?", "recorded_at": "2026-06-26T09:15:49.489991Z", "run_id": "01KW1KDHVGWZ0QERDMV1CRJ15S", "state_entered_at": "2026-06-26T09:15:49.488836Z", "step_id": "plan.windows-compat.normalize-base"}}
